This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a strategy for training deep ensembles with a diversity function regularization to improve the calibration property while maintaining a similar prediction accuracy. Additionally, the paper involves the use of deep neural network models, which are commonly used in machine learning. 

It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as the paper involves improving the reliability of uncertainty estimates in predictions, which is an important aspect of AI. 

Furthermore, the paper could be categorized under cs.CV (Computer Vision) as deep neural networks are commonly used in computer vision tasks, and the proposed strategy could be applied to improve the calibration of models used in computer vision. 

The paper could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it involves the use of deep neural networks and proposes a strategy for improving their calibration. 

Finally, it could be categorized under cs.CL (Computation and Language) as the proposed strategy could be applied to improve the calibration of models used in natural language processing tasks, which is a common application of deep neural networks.
